  "texts": [
    "Silva et al. (2024) suggests that providing students with clear guidelines on using ChatGPT can be beneficial to support their critical-thinking and problem-solving skills during programming learning.",
    "Yilmaz and Yilmaz (2023b) emphasize the importance of gaining prompt writing skills for students and AI-literacy for teachers to benefit from ChatGPT in a more efficient and effective way.",
    "While interacting with AI-driven tools, students can display different behaviors, and reveal distinct profiles and patterns in terms of their engagement and utilization (Stojanov et al., 2024; Wang et al., 2023).",
    "For example, in programming, some students may use AI primarily to get information without much questioning, while others might use it for improving their knowledge or conceptual understanding (Stojanov et al., 2024).",
    "Besides, students' interaction with AI can be influenced by their prior knowledge about the subject matter (Xia et al., 2023)."
  ],
